23. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bentham (1841: 390)" authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1841" box="[178,639,1958,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[178,392,1958,1985]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Mimosa verrucosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[399,639,1958,1984]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" pagination="390" refId="ref14600" refString="Bentham, G. (1841) Mimosa verrucosa Benth. Journal of Botany Botanical Miscellany 4 (31): 390." type="journal article" year="1841">Bentham (1841: 390)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1451,2030,2092]" lastBlockId="15.[136,1452,158,581]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,200,2030,2056]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Trees</emphasis>
, branches glandular, inermous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[547,642,2030,2056]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Nectary</emphasis>
absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[729,824,2030,2056]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Stipules</emphasis>
lateral, narrow-triangular. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1116,1198,2030,2056]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Leaves</emphasis>
bipinnate, paripinnate, 10–18–foliolate, leaflets opposite, oblong, venation actinodromous, translucid punctuation absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1222,1380,2066,2092]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Inflorescence</emphasis>
spike, axillary. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,329,158,184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Flowers</emphasis>
sessile, actinomorphic, isostemonous; calyx gamosepalous, sepals 4, corolla gamopetalous, tubular, rose, petals 4; androecium dialystaminous, homodinamous, anthers longitudinal; ovary superior, sessile, pluriovulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,198,230,256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Fruit</emphasis>
craspedium, stipitate, linear, plane, margin constricted, epicarp verrucose, brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1123,1190,230,256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Seeds</emphasis>
not observed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
